ence"><a href="#cite_note-116">[111]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-117" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-117">[112]</a></sup><sup class="noprint Inline-Template" style="white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Identifying_reliable_sources" title="Wikipedia:Identifying reliable sources"><span title="The material near this tag may rely on an unreliable source. (November 2013)">unreliable source?</span></a></i>]</sup> He massacred thousands of them.<sup id="cite_ref-118" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-118">[113]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-119" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-119">[114]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-120" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-120">[115]</a></sup><sup class="noprint Inline-Template" style="white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Identifying_reliable_sources" title="Wikipedia:Identifying reliable sources"><span title="The material near this tag may rely on an unreliable source. (November 2013)">unreliable source?</span></a></i>]</sup> He restricted the freedom of many <a href="/wiki/Concubinage" title="Concubinage">concubines</a> and killed several<sup class="noprint Inline-Template" style="white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style/Words_to_watch#Unsupported_attributions" title="Wikipedia:Manual of Style/Words to watch"><span title="The material near this tag possibly uses too-vague attribution or weasel words. (November 2013)">who?</span></a></i>]</sup>.<sup id="cite_ref-121" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-121">[116]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-122" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-122">[117]</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-123" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-123">[118]</a></sup><sup class="noprint Inline-Template" style="white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Identifying_reliable_sources" title="Wikipedia:Identifying reliable sources"><span title="The material near this tag may rely on an unreliable source. (November 2013)">unreliable source?</span></a></i>]</sup> He also forced many of them<sup class="noprint Inline-Template" style="white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style/Words_to_watch#Unsupported_attributions" title="Wikipedia:Manual of Style/Words to watch"><span title="The material near this tag possibly uses too-vague attribution or weasel words. (November 2013)">who?</span></a></i>]</sup> to commit suicide and ordered that they will be buried with him after his death.<sup id="cite_ref-124" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-124">[119]</a></sup><sup class="noprint Inline-Template" style="white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Identifying_reliable_sources" title="Wikipedia:Identifying reliable sources"><span title="The material near this tag may rely on an unreliable source. (November 2013)">unreliable source?</span></a></i>]</sup> He had several Korean concubines, including Lady Han, who bore him a son, and Lady Gong.<sup id="cite_ref-125" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-125">[120]</a></sup></p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Sons">Sons</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Hongwu_Emperor&amp;action=edit&amp;section=22" title="Edit section: Sons">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<table class="wikitable">\n<tr>\n<th>Number</th>\n<th>Name</th>\n<th>Formal Title</th>\n<th>Born</th>\n<th>Died</th>\n<th>Mother</th>\n<th>Spouse</th>\n<th>Issue</th>\n<th>Notes</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Zhu_Biao" title="Zhu Biao">Zhu Biao</a><br />\n\xe6\x9c\xb1\xe6\xa8\x99</td>\n<td>Crown Prince Yiwen<br />\n\xe6\x87\xbf\xe6\x96\x87\xe5\xa4\xaa\xe5\xad\x90</td>\n<td>10 October 1355</td>\n<td>17 May 1392</td>\n<td>Empress Xiaocigao</td>\n<td>Lady Chang<br />\nLady L\xc3\xbc</td>\n<td>Zhu Xiongying, Prince Huai of Yu<br />\n<a href="/wiki/Jianwen_Emperor" title="Jianwen Emperor">Zhu Yunwen, Jianwen Emperor</a><br />\nZhu Yuntong, Prince of Wu<br />\nZhu Yunjian, Pri