></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>12</td>\n<td>Princess Zhenyi of Yongjia<br />\n\xe6\xb0\xb8\xe5\x98\x89\xe8\xb2\x9e\xe6\x87\xbf\xe5\x85\xac\xe4\xb8\xbb</td>\n<td>1376</td>\n<td>12 October 1455</td>\n<td>23 November 1389</td>\n<td>Guo Zhen<br />\n\xe9\x83\xad\xe9\x8e\xae<br />\n(son of Guo Ying, Marquess of Wuding)</td>\n<td>Guo Zhensi<br />\n\xe9\x83\xad\xe7\x8f\x8d\xe5\x97\xa3</td>\n<td>Consort Hui</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>13</td>\n<td>none</td>\n<td>\xe2\x80\x93</td>\n<td>\xe2\x80\x93</td>\n<td>none</td>\n<td>none</td>\n<td>none</td>\n<td>\xe2\x80\x93</td>\n<td>Died young</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>14</td>\n<td>Princess Hanshan<br />\n\xe5\x90\xab\xe5\xb1\xb1\xe5\x85\xac\xe4\xb8\xbb</td>\n<td>1381</td>\n<td>18 October 1462</td>\n<td>11 September 1394</td>\n<td>Yin Qing<br />\n\xe5\xb0\xb9\xe6\xb8\x85</td>\n<td>\xe2\x80\x93</td>\n<td>Consort Han</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>15</td>\n<td>Princess Ruyang<br />\n\xe6\xb1\x9d\xe9\x99\xbd\xe5\x85\xac\xe4\xb8\xbb</td>\n<td>\xe2\x80\x93</td>\n<td>\xe2\x80\x93</td>\n<td>23 August 1394</td>\n<td>Xie Da<br />\n\xe8\xac\x9d\xe9\x81\x94</td>\n<td>\xe2\x80\x93</td>\n<td>Consort Hui</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>16</td>\n<td>Princess Baoqing<br />\n\xe5\xaf\xb6\xe6\x85\xb6\xe5\x85\xac\xe4\xb8\xbb</td>\n<td>1394</td>\n<td>1433</td>\n<td>1413</td>\n<td>Zhao Hui<br />\n\xe8\xb6\x99\xe8\xbc\x9d</td>\n<td>\xe2\x80\x93</td>\n<td>Beauty Lady Zhang</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="In_popular_culture">In popular culture</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Hongwu_Emperor&amp;action=edit&amp;section=24" title="Edit section: In popular culture">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<dl>\n<dt>Novels</dt>\n</dl>\n<ul>\n<li><i><a href="/wiki/The_Heaven_Sword_and_Dragon_Saber" title="The Heaven Sword and Dragon Saber">The Heaven Sword and Dragon Saber</a></i> (\xe5\x80\x9a\xe5\xa4\xa9\xe5\xb1\xa0\xe9\xbe\x8d\xe8\xa8\x98), a 1961\xe2\x80\x9363 <i><a href="/wiki/Wuxia" title="Wuxia">wuxia</a></i> novel by <a href="/wiki/Jin_Yong" title="Jin Yong">Louis Cha</a>. Zhu Yuanzhang <a href="/wiki/List_of_The_Heaven_Sword_and_Dragon_Saber_characters#Ming_Cult" title="List of The Heaven Sword and Dragon Saber characters">appears as a minor character in the novel</a>. Zhu Yuanzhang has been portrayed by various actors in the films and television series adapted from this novel.</li>\n</ul>\n<dl>\n<dt>Television series</dt>\n</dl>\n<ul>\n<li><i>Born to be a King</i> (\xe5\xa4\xa7\xe6\x98\x8e\xe7\xbe\xa4\xe8\x8b\xb1), a 1987 Hong Kong television series produced by <a href="/wiki/Television_Broadcasts_Limited" class="mw-redirect" title="Television Broadcasts Limited">TVB</a> and starring <a href="/wiki/Simon_Yam" title="Simon Yam">Simon Yam</a> as Zhu Yuanzhang.</li>\n<li><i>Zhu Yuanzhang</i> (\xe6\x9c\xb1\xe5\x85\x83\xe7\x92\x8b), a 1993 Chinese television series produced by <a href="/wiki/Beijing_Media_Network" title="Beijing Media Network">Beijing TV</a> and starring L\xc3\xbc Qi as Zhu Yuanzhang.</li>\n<li><i>Empress Ma With Great Feet</i> (\xe5\xa4\xa7\xe8\x85\xb3\xe9\xa6\xac\xe7\x9a\x87\xe5\x90\x8e), a 2002 Chinese television series about Zhu Yuanzhang\'s wife, <a href="/wiki/Empress_Ma_(Hongwu)" title="Empress Ma (Hongwu)">Empress Ma</a>. <a href="/wiki/Tang_Guoqiang" title="Tang Guoqiang">Tang Guoqiang</a> starred as Zhu Yuanzhang.</li>\n<li><i><a href="/wiki/Chuanqi_Huangdi_Zhu_Yuanzhang" title="Chuanqi Huangdi Zhu Yuanzhang">Chuanqi Huangdi Zhu Yuanzhang</a></i> (\xe5\x82\xb3\xe5\xa5\x87\xe7\x9a\x87\xe5\xb8\x9d\xe6\x9c\xb1\xe5\x85\x83\xe7\x92\x8b), a 2006 Chinese television series starring <a href="/wiki/Chen_Baoguo" title="Chen Baoguo">Chen Baoguo</a> as Zhu Yuanzhang.</li>\n<li><i><a href="/wiki/Founding_Emperor_of_Ming_Dynasty" title="Founding Emperor of Ming Dynasty">Founding Emperor of Ming Dynasty</a></i> (\xe6\x9c\xb1\xe5\x85\x83\xe7\x92\x8b), a 2006 Chinese television series directed by <a href="/wiki/Feng_Xiaoning" title="Feng Xiaoning">Feng Xiaoning</a> and starring <a href="/wiki/Hu_Jun" title="Hu Jun">Hu Jun</a> as Zhu Yuanzhang.</li>\n<li><i>The Legendary Liu Bowen</i> (\xe7\xa5\x9e\xe6\xa9\x9f\xe5\xa6\x99\xe7\xae\x97\xe5\x8a\x89\xe4\xbc\xaf\xe6\xba\xab), a 2006\xe2\x80\x932008 Taiwanese television series about Zhu Yuanzhang\'s adviser, <a href="/wiki/Liu_Bowen" title="Liu Bowen">Liu Bowen</a>. It was produced by <a href="/wiki/Taiwan_Television" title="Taiwan Television">TTV</a> and starred Huo Zhengqi as Zhu Yuanzhang.</li>\n<li><i>Zhenming Tianzi</i> (\xe7\x9c\x9f\xe5\x91\xbd\xe5\xa4\xa9\xe5\xad\x90), a 2015 Chinese television series produced by Jian Yuanxin and starring Zhang Zhuowen as Zhu Yuanzhang.</li>\n<li><i><a href="/wiki/Love_Through_Different_Times" title="Love Through Different Times">Love Through Different Times</a></i> (\xe7\xa9\xbf\xe8\xb6\x8a\xe6\x97\xb6\xe7\xa9\xba\xe7\x9a\x84\xe7\x88\xb1\xe6\x81\x8b), a 2002 Chinese television comedy-drama that is considered the first time-travel television series produced in mainland China.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="See_also">See also</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Hongwu_Emperor&amp;action=edit&amp;section=25" title="Edit section: See also">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role="navigation" aria-label="Portals" class="noprint portal plainlist tright" style="margin:0.5em 0 0.5em 1em;border:solid #aaa 1px">\n<ul style="display:table;box-sizing:border-box;padding:0.1em;max-width:175px;background:#f9f9f9;font-size:85%;line-height:110%;font-style:italic;font-weight:bold">\n<li style="display:table-row"><span style="display:table-cell;padding:0.2em;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center"><img alt="flag" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fa/Flag_of_the_People%27s_Republic_of_China.svg/32px-Flag_of_the_People%27s_Republic_of_China.svg.png" width="32" height="21" class="noviewer thumbborder" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fa/Flag_of_the_People%27s_Republic_of_China.svg/48px-Flag_of_the_People%27s_Republic_of_China.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fa/Flag_of_the_People%27s_Republic_of_China.svg/64px-Flag_of_the_People%27s_Republic_of_China.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="900" data-file-height="600" /></span><span style="display:table-cell;padding:0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em;vertical-align:middle"><a href="/wiki/Portal:China" title="Portal:China">China portal</a></span></li>\n<li style="display:table-row"><span style="display:table-cell;padding:0.2em;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center"><a href="/wiki/File:Crown_of_Saint_Edward_Heraldry.svg" class="image"><img alt="icon" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Crown_of_Saint_Edward_Heraldry.svg/30px-Crown_of_Saint_Edward_Heraldry.svg.png" width="30" height="28" class="noviewer" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Crown_of_Saint_Edward_Heraldry.svg/45px-Crown_of_Saint_Edward_Heraldry.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Crown_of_Saint_Edward_Heraldry.svg/60px-Crown_of_Saint_Edward_Heraldry.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="115" data-file-height="108" /></a></span><span style="display:table-cell;padding:0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em;vertical-align:middle"><a href="/wiki/Portal:Monarchy" title="Portal:Monarchy">Monarchy portal</a></span></li>\n<li style="display:table-row"><span style="display:table-cell;padding:0.2em;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/P_history.svg/31px-P_history.svg.png" width="31" height="28" class="noviewer" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/P_history.svg/47px-P_history.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/48/P_history.svg/62px-P_history.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="400" data-file-height="360" /></span><span style="display:table-cell;padding:0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em;vertical-align:middle"><a href="/wiki/Portal:History" title="Portal:History">History portal</a></span></li>\n<li style="display:table-row"><span style="display:table-cell;padding:0.2em;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/69/P_vip.svg/28px-P_vip.svg.png" width="28" height="28" class="noviewer" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/69/P_vip.svg/41px-P_vip.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/69/P_vip.svg/55px-P_vip.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="1911" data-file-height="1944" /></span><span style="display:table-cell;padding:0.2em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em;vertical-align:middle"><a href="/wiki/Portal:Biography" title="Portal:Biography">Biography portal</a></span></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Huang_Ming_Zu_Xun" class="mw-redirect" title="Huang Ming Zu Xun">Huang Ming Zu Xun</a>, the "Ancestral Instructions" written by the Hongwu Emperor to guide his descendants</li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Ming_Xiaoling_Mausoleum" title="Ming Xiaoling Mausoleum">Ming Xiaoling Mausoleum</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Rags_to_riches" title="Rags to riches">Rags to riches</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Sino-Tibetan_relations_during_the_Ming_dynasty" title="Sino-Tibetan relations during the Ming dynasty">Sino-Tibetan relations during the Ming dynasty</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Hongwu_Emperor&amp;action=edit&amp;section=26" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class="reflist" style="list-style-type: decimal;">\n<div class="mw-references-wrap">\n<ol class="references">\n<li id="cite_note-1"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The Hongwu Emperor was already in control of <a href="/wiki/Nanjing" title="Nanjing">Nanjing</a> since 1356 and was conferred the title of "<a href="/w/index.php?title=Duke_of_Wu&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Duke of Wu (page does not exist)">Duke of Wu</a>" (<span lang="zh" xml:lang="zh">\xe5\x90\xb3\xe5\x9c\x8b\xe5\x85\xac</span>) by the rebel leader <a href="/w/index.php?title=Han_Lin%27er&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Han Lin\'er (page does not exist)">Han Lin\'er</a> (<span lang="zh" xml:lang="zh">\xe9\x9f\x93\xe6\x9e\x97\xe5\x85\x92</span>) in 1361. He started autonomous rule as the self-proclaimed "<a href="/wiki/Prince_of_Wu" class="mw-redirect" title="Prince of Wu">Prince of Wu</a>" (<span lang="zh" xml:lang="zh">\xe5\x90\xb3\xe7\x8e\x8b</span>) on 4 February 1364. He was proclaimed emperor on 23 January 1368 and established the <a href="/wiki/Ming_dynasty" title="Ming dynasty">Ming dynasty</a> on that same day.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-Different_from_the_above-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Different_from_the_above_2-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Different_from_the_above_2-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Different_from_the_above_2-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">Different from the above</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-3"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Name given by his parents at birth and used only inside the family and friends. This birth name, which means "double eight", was allegedly given to him because the combined age of his parents when he was born was 88 years.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-4"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">He was known as "Zhu Xingzong" when he reached adulthood and renamed himself "Zhu Yuanzhang" in 1352 when he started to become famous among the rebel leaders.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Upon his successful usurpation in 1402, the <a href="/wiki/Yongle_Emperor" title="Yongle Emperor">Yongle Emperor</a> voided the Jianwen era of <a href="/wiki/Jianwen_Emperor" title="Jianwen Emperor">his predecessor</a> and continued the Hongwu era posthumously until the next <a href="/wiki/Chinese_New_Year" title="Chinese New Year">New Year</a> when his own new era was declared. This dating continued for a few of his successors until the Jianwen era was re\xc3\xabstablished in the late 16th century.</span></li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n</div>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="References">References</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Hongwu_Emperor&amp;action=edit&amp;section=27" title="Edit section: References">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<table role="presentation" class="mbox-small plainlinks sistersitebox" style="background-color:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;color:#000">\n<tr>\n<td class="mbox-image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.svg.png" width="30" height="40" class="noviewer" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/45px-Commons-logo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/59px-Commons-logo.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="1024" data-file-height="1376" /></td>\n<td class="mbox-text plainlist"><a href="/wiki/Wikimedia_Commons" title="Wikimedia Commons">Wikimedia Commons</a> has media related to:\n<div style="margin-left: 10px;"><i><b><a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/%E6%98%8E%E5%A4%AA%E7%A5%96" class="extiw" title="commons:\xe6\x98\x8e\xe5\xa4\xaa\xe7\xa5\x96">\xe6\x98\x8e\xe5\xa4\xaa\xe7\xa5\x96</a></b></i> (<a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:Search/Category